BEGIN_TEXT

Using the chain rule, find \( \frac{d}{dx}(\log x) \).
$BR
(Recall \( \log x=\log_{10}{x}. \))

$PAR
\( \frac{d}{dx}(\log x) = \) \{ ans_rule(65) \}

END_TEXT


ANS( fun_cmp( "1/(ln(10)*x)" ) );

SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$PAR SOLUTION $PAR

Let
\( g(x) = \log x \).
Then
\( 10^{g(x)} = x \).
Differentiating,
\( (\ln 10)(10^{g(x)}) g'(x) = 1 \), so 
\( g'(x) = \frac{1}{(\ln 10)(10^{g(x)})} \), or 
\( g'(x) = \frac{1}{(\ln 10)x} \).

END_SOLUTION


